    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "data": {
            "children": [
              {
                "data": {
                  "value": "The residuals are defined as the difference between the derivatives of our solution and rhs of the ODE system. We use relative residuals, i.e., normalized by 1 + np.abs(f). RMS values are computed as sqrt from the normalized integrals of the squared relative residuals over each interval. Integrals are estimated using 5-point Lobatto quadrature , we use the fact that residuals at the mesh nodes are identically zero."
                },
                "type": "Words"
              }
            ]
          },
          "type": "Paragraph"
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "children": [
              {
                "data": {
                  "value": "In [2] they don't normalize integrals by interval lengths, which gives a higher rate of convergence of the residuals by the factor of h**0.5. I chose to do such normalization for an ease of interpretation of return values as RMS estimates."
                },
                "type": "Words"
              }
            ]
          },
          "type": "Paragraph"
        }
      ],
